# CIROH DevCon 2026 — TethysDash + MCP Workshop — environment template.
#
# Copy this to .env and fill in concrete values BEFORE running setup.sh.
# .env is gitignored; .env.example is committed.
#
# Maintainer pins these in docs/pre-conditions.md and keeps the two files
# in sync per event tag. Participants generally do not edit this file —
# they copy it to .env and adjust VM_HOST if they want the tunnel.sh
# helper to remember their VM.

# ---- Repo refs (branch or SHA — Unit 0 Q7 + Q7b + Q7d) --------------------
# Each *_REF below can be EITHER a branch name (default) OR a 40-char SHA
# (for event-day reproducibility). setup.sh auto-detects:
#   - Branch refs:  setup.sh ff-pulls to the latest tip on every run.
#                   Easier to maintain — upstream fixes propagate with a
#                   plain `bash scripts/setup.sh && docker compose up -d`.
#   - SHA refs:     setup.sh checks out the SHA (detached HEAD). Use for
#                   event-day pinning if you want frozen behavior.
#
# Default values pin to branch tips appropriate for dev workshop use.
# Replace with a SHA before the event if you want cohort-wide reproducibility.
#
# TETHYSDASH_REF: lives on tethysplatform/tethysapp-tethys_dash. The
# feature/tethysdash-mcp-server branch is the team's MCP integration
# branch and includes commit 186fb37 (PR #6 — anonymous
# /runtime-plugins/list/ endpoint) that the standalone tethysdash_mcps
# server needs. See docs/pre-conditions.md Q7.
TETHYSDASH_REF=feature/tethysdash-mcp-server
NRDS_MCPS_REF=main
TETHYSDASH_MCPS_REF=main

# ---- Image tags (per-event publish) ---------------------------------------
# The workshop maintainer publishes ghcr.io/aquaveo/ciroh-devcon-2026:<tag>
# from this repo's publish-image.yml workflow before the event. Set IMAGE_TAG
# to the published tag for the current event (e.g., v2026.05). Avoid
# :latest in participant config to keep the cohort on a deterministic image.
IMAGE_TAG=v2026.05

# The nrds-mcps image is published by the upstream nrds_mcps repo's own
# release pipeline (not by this workshop). Pin to a specific version tag
# for the event (e.g., v0.1.4). `latest` works in development but does NOT
# guarantee participant cohort consistency; replace before the event.
NRDS_MCPS_IMAGE_TAG=latest

# The tethysdash-mcps image is published by the upstream tethysdash_mcps
# repo's release.yml on every `v*` tag push (multi-arch amd64+arm64). Pin
# to a specific version tag for the event (e.g., v0.2.0). Same `latest`
# caveat as NRDS_MCPS_IMAGE_TAG — fine in dev, replace before the event.
TETHYSDASH_MCPS_IMAGE_TAG=latest

# ---- tunnel.sh convenience ------------------------------------------------
# Optional. If set, tunnel.sh skips the interactive prompt and uses this host.
# Format: "<user>@<vm-host>" e.g. "ttalbot@workshop-vm-12.access.example.org"
# Leave blank to make tunnel.sh prompt at runtime.
VM_HOST=
